# Custom /etc/hosts bind-mounted into the proxy and conference containers.
#
# Why this exists: stock Linphone clients default to Belledonne's PUBLIC
# resource-list server (sips:rls@sip.linphone.org) for the friends list. The
# proxy forwards those SUBSCRIBEs out, leaking account existence, online
# status, server IP and timing to a third party.
#
# Why a bind-mount rather than extra_hosts or the host's /etc/hosts:
#   - the host's /etc/hosts does NOT reach containers (Docker generates its own)
#   - compose extra_hosts silently DROPS IPv6 entries (bracketed or otherwise)
#   - an IPv4-only entry does NOT suppress the AAAA lookup: glibc still falls
#     through to DNS and returns the real IPv6 address (verified)
# Both families must therefore be pinned here explicitly.
#
# 0.0.0.0 and 100:: (RFC 6666 discard-only) are unroutable as destinations, so
# connections fail fast. Do NOT use 127.0.0.1/::1 - the proxy listens on 5061
# and would receive its own out-of-domain SUBSCRIBE.

127.0.0.1	localhost
::1		localhost ip6-localhost ip6-loopback
ff02::1		ip6-allnodes
ff02::2		ip6-allrouters

0.0.0.0		sip.linphone.org sip11.linphone.org
100::		sip.linphone.org sip11.linphone.org
